headline: Why Corporate America Ended Its Firing Freeze
summary: The job market has softened in recent months, marking a safer environment for companies to start streamlining their workforces. A host of them have pounced, including Amazon, UPS, Target and Meta Platforms, which collectively announced tens of thousands of layoffs in recent weeks.

headline: Target is a dumpster fire that needs to be put out
summary: Experts will tell you that timing the market doesn't work. I tend to agree, but only to a point. And I'm usually not one to shy away from buying a stock near its 52-week low if I feel it's a solid business with lots of potential that's maybe going through a rough patch. Target is not that company. ...
